{"word":"εὐοδόω","slug":"εὐοδόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐοδόω</b></el> <el>(εὐ-οδόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to help on the way</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to have a prosperous journey</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to prosper, be successful</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}